Angie Arrien: Okay, now the focus of tonight is to share with you probably the oldest interpretation spread in all of Tarot applications of any kind. What this is based on, originally, is what's been known as the Celtic Cross Spread. Originally, this has been a combination, this spread, which I have permutated or have made a change so that it applies more to the now, is that I've taken this old Celtic Cross spread, which is really a combination of the Celtic Cross, the equidistant cross, and the ladder. In the time of the Druids, which the Celtic Cross comes from, the Celtic Cross literally was a symbol of whatever we were experiencing inside the vertical line of the cross, we must demonstrate outside. Whatever we demonstrate outside creates certain effects, which is the ladder. Whatever we build, which is a symbol of the ladder, there are certain effects, and that's the rung of the ladder. Each side of the ladder is literally our dynamic and magnetic energies. One side of the ladder is how we start things, initiate things, which is our masculine or our dynamic energy, the other side of the ladder is how we complete whatever we set into motion, which is the feminine. The process in between, the rungs in between, are what we reach for, which could be a symbol of goals, which could be a symbol of certain effects, which could be a symbol of ascendancy, wanting to move higher in our evolutionary growth process.

Angie Arrien: In the traditional reading spread, really the classic reading spread, is this spread, it's the cross with the ladder. What I've done is literally called this the whole person spread, taking it from ancient Egypt. This really is the Druids application. What I've taken is the Druid application plus the Egyptian, and the Egyptian plus the balance with the human form, because the cross literally is a symbol of the human form, what's inside we reach out for or we apply, and then that causes certain effects, which is the ladder. That's one reason why I call this the whole person spread, rather than the self-cross spread. One reason for that is to take it out of the esoterica, and once again showing that symbols are living, symbols are to be used, symbols are to be applied, symbols facilitate internal processes, they also facilitate external processes. Giving them a more updated name such as the whole person spread, I feel does that. The old Celtic Cross spread many of the positions are the same, but what I've done again is give them newer meaning or newer application. For example, the torso is the heart. The number one position of the whole person spread is literally the heart in the past, our emotional patterns of the past. All of those meanings are that you have a number one on the position and then you have the numbers that are corresponding at the bottom of page one, it's the heart and the past.

Angie Arrien: Literally, whatever comes up there for a person indicates what's happened to them before, how they may have handled things emotionally in the past. It's more emotional past patterns than it is current patterns. Again, you would take the number off the top of the card and you would either go back that this was your emotional nature, or pattern that may go back as far as eight years ago because here we have the Eight of Disks. You would indicate to them that perhaps in 1972, 8 years ago, was a time that you were emotionally prudent, cautious, careful, needing to utilize wisdom, making sure all bases recovered. Then you can take the astrological aspects, Sun in Virgo, and you can also indicate that somewhere in the past eight years, taking the number off the top of the card, there may have been an important relationship with the Virgo person, someone born August 21st to September 21st. In all interpretation, which is on the second page of your worksheet, is that the first thing you always consider in any interpretation process is the position first, and you would tell the individual the meaning of the position. The next thing that you would indicate is the state of consciousness. You'd look to see what suit it is. It's the next thing you look to. This indicates that this person's state of consciousness, emotionally in the past, since it was Disks, it was very practical, needing to utilize really practical common sense application of their emotional nature. The first thing is the position. The second thing that you'll take a look at is the suit for an indicator. The third thing that you do is take a look at the general meaning of the card, which is prudent, caution, wisdom, carefulness. The last thing that you might want to take a look at is the astrological symbolism on the card to indicate another probability for the individual. That's a lot of information. Usually, when you take a person back in time when you suggest a date.

Angie Arrien: For all of us, it takes some time to reconstruct the past, and so often when you mention a date, you've lost the person at that point in time to anything else that you want to say after that. Often I found that that's the last thing on a card symbol that I'll mention before I go on to the next position because anything that I would say after I mention a date, and that's why usually, we have people bring tapes so that it can be taped so that they can listen to it. Because whenever I mention a date, it takes them back to that point in time and they're gone so that they will not really hear what you've got to say following that, and so to be aware of that. Usually date factors or like a Virgo person, because all of a sudden their mind's going to go through all their friends and their birthdays, and so that anytime after that or any statements after that is also going to be somewhat lost. Be aware of that as well.

Angie Arrien: I give all the probabilities. For example, I'll go back to the longest time first, I'll say, "This could have been eight years ago, or when you were eight years old, and it may have come up for you in a different way eight months ago, for you to consider," and give them all those checkpoints. Then as a result that then it leaves it to them to call up their own experiences so that they can see how that symbol applies to them directly, rather than me saying to them, or you saying to your client very definitively, "It was 1972," because that's a natural setup. It's not how symbols work. If you give them all the probabilities, there's going to be one within that probability that is going to work. I found that to be the case. Give them all of those possibilities, because for one person it may be finances, for another person, it may be health, and for a third person, it may neither be help nor finances, but it could be an external situation. All of those options, again, is going to to give them a picture of their probabilities of what they're creating. The symbol of turning the card over, much like in the Book of Thoth, when you would turn a page, it was a symbol of revelation. Something hidden was about to be revealed. It literally is a very old ritual, and it's part of the ritual practice.
